# Lenar Component Rules

## Component Boundaries
- Keep presentation components in `components/`; avoid direct DB calls inside UI components.
- Prefer Server Components for read-heavy views; use Client Components only for interactivity.
- Mark interactive files with `"use client"` only when required.

## Composition and Reuse
- Build from shadcn/ui primitives before creating custom low-level controls.
- Keep components small and single-purpose; extract shared UI when repeated.
- Prefer prop-driven composition over tightly coupled parent-child logic.

## Props and Types
- Type all props explicitly with interfaces or type aliases.
- Avoid `any`; use unions/enums/literals for known states.
- Keep prop APIs minimal; pass only what the child needs.

## State and Effects
- Keep local UI state in components; avoid global state unless clearly necessary.
- Use React Hook Form + Zod for form components and validation flows.
- Avoid unnecessary `useEffect`; derive values from props/state when possible.

## UX and Accessibility
- Use semantic HTML and accessible shadcn patterns by default.
- Always provide labels, helper text, and error messages for form inputs.
- Handle loading, empty, and error UI states for dashboard, lessons, and tasks.

## Styling
- Use Tailwind utility classes; keep class strings readable and grouped.
- Reuse consistent spacing, typography, and card/list patterns across screens.
- Use `lucide-react` for icons to maintain visual consistency.

## Performance
- Avoid heavy client-side logic in top-level layout components.
- Memoize only when profiling indicates repeated expensive renders.
- Keep lists keyed by stable IDs, never array indices for dynamic lists.
